<div style="height:100px"></div>
<h2>APIs</h2><br />

<pre style="font-size:15px;font-family:'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;background-color:white;word-break:inherit">
Currently we have 2 API's exposed to the users and website owners.
1. Bookkmarks API 
2. Reports API

Please make a separate request from "Contact Us" section to gain access to API. 
We will get back to you to setup clientid along with the key needed to access the API's.

Below is the sample glimpse of request and response of API, we will provide you with detail documentation to access the API.


<b>Bookkmarks API</b> - User can get all his/her bookkmarks in the form of JSON or XML

                <b>URI</b>: <a style="text-decoration:underline;color:blue" href="https://bookkmark.com/api/1/GetBookkmarks?action=fetch">https://bookkmark.com/api/1/GetBookkmarks?action=fetch</a>

                <b>Method</b>: Get

                <b>Request</b>:
                {
                "spec":
                {
                "filter": "servicePoint.client.id=='xxxxxxxxxx'",
                "include": "id"
                }
                }

                <b>Response</b>:
                {
                "objs" : [ { "name" : "google",
                             "url" : "http://google.com",
                "version" : xxxx,
                } ],
                "count" : 1,
                "hasMore" : false
                }



<b>Reports API</b> - Site owners can get all the information about the user bookmarks like bookmarked date, user location, name, url and more

                <b>URI</b>: <a style="text-decoration:underline;color:blue" href="https://bookkmark.com/api/1/GetReports?action=fetch">https://bookkmark.com/api/1/GetReports?action=fetch</a>

                <b>Method</b>: Get

                <b>Request</b>:
                {
                    "spec":
                    {
                        "filter": "servicePoint.client.id=='xxxxxxxxxx'",
                        "include": "id"
                    }
                }

                <b>Response</b>:
                {
                "objs" : [ { "url" : "http://google.com",
                             "location" : "San Francisco, CA",
                             "created_date" : "xx/xx/xx",
                "version" : xxxx,
                } ],
                "count" : 1,
                "hasMore" : false
                }




</pre>